locationDescriptionGae: Iarrann sí, 'Cad a thugann isteach inár gcónaíodh dorcha thú, gan choinne?
locationDescriptionEng: You sense the presence of the veiled ones.
She asks, 'What brings you to our dark haven, uninvited?
gaeTurnToPage: Tagann meangadh gáire uirthí. 'Frog anois thú,' arsa sí. Laighsfaidh braon ó Pol an Púca thú. go dté tú slán.
Sna garráin naofa, ciúnann gáire na síoga.Feicim Bád le seoltaí iarainn.
engTurnToPage: The witch smiles. 'You are now a frog. A drop from Pollapooka will cure you. Good day.'
I hear conflict in the Otherworld.  I see Ships with Iron sails.

locationDescriptionEng: The air is filled with the sweet scent of wildflowers.
In the distance, a harp beckons you.
At the summit, you come across an ancient harp resting against a stone.
locationDescriptionGae: Líonann an t-aer le boladh milis, bláthanna fiáine Tulaigh an Eallaigh.
Tagann ceol cruit, ag glaoch ar an ngaoth.
Ag bárr an Tullach, tagann tú ar cruit ársa, ag luí i gcoinne cloch.
answEng: Place your hand upon the harp
engTurnToPage: As you touch the harp, a haunting tune fills the air.

locationDescriptionEng: The rolling green hills seem to stretch forever.
locationDescriptionGae: Cuireann an gaoth cheol bínn chugat.
Téann tú i dtreo an tsráidbhaile,
tuithí ceann tuí, ceangailte go héifeachtach.

locationDescriptionEng: where the rare goosander is seen in winter
The ancient and imposing Fort of the King, stands proudly atop a hill.
As you approach, you notice a tense atmosphere enveloping the fort. Whispers of clandestine meetings and hidden agendas reach your ears, painting a picture of political intrigue.
At the entrance, two guards in elaborate armor stand watch.
answEng: Persuade the guards to let you in
Sneak into the fort under the cover of darkness
